03/10/2002
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- The constituent session of Macedonia's fourth parliamentary assembly is to open Thursday (3 October) afternoon. Following the 15 September elections, a total of 17 political parties will be represented in parliament - ten of them are part of the For Macedonia Together coalition, which won a total of 60 seats in the 120-seat legislature. Branko Crvenkovski, leader of the coalition's dominant party, the Social Democratic Alliance of Macedonia (SDSM), confirmed Wednesday that SDSM would seek to keep the key position of Parliamentary Chairman for itself. He added that negotiations with the ethnic Albanian Democratic Union for Integration (DUI) on forming a coalition government would begin Friday. (Utrinski Vesnik, Vest, Nova Makedonija - 03/10/02; MIA - 02/10/02)
